data.name: Classic Beef Wellington with a Red Wine Reduction and Roasted Vegetables
data.quickTastyDescription: A show-stopping beef Wellington encased in flaky pastry, paired with a rich red wine reduction and seasonal roasted vegetables.
detailedCookingInstructions: Sear the beef tenderloin in a hot skillet for 2-3 minutes on each side until browned. Season with salt and pepper, then brush with Dijon mustard. Let it cool.
In the same skillet, sauté finely chopped mushrooms in butter until all moisture evaporates; season with salt and pepper. Cool the mixture.

Lay out prosciutto slices on a piece of plastic wrap, slightly overlapping. Spread the mushroom mixture over the prosciutto, then place the beef on top and roll tightly using the plastic wrap. Chill for 15 minutes.
Roll out puff pastry on a floured surface. Remove the beef roll from plastic wrap and place it in the center of the pastry. Wrap the pastry around the beef, sealing the edges with egg yolk.
Place the wrapped beef on a baking sheet, brush with egg yolk, and make a few slits on top for steam to escape. Bake for 25-30 minutes or until the pastry is golden brown and beef is medium-rare.
While the Wellington bakes, prepare the red wine reduction by simmering red wine in a saucepan until reduced by half; whisk in butter to finish.
Toss carrots and asparagus in olive oil, salt, and pepper. Roast in the oven for the last 15 minutes of Wellington cooking time until tender.
Slice the beef Wellington and serve with the red wine reduction and roasted vegetables.
data.detailedName: Classic Beef Wellington with Red Wine Reduction and Seasonal Roasted Vegetables
data.modifiersForBase: served with red wine reduction and assorted roasted vegetables
